Spawn an independent worker process. By default uses a built-in agent with {tools} tools. The worker only sees the task description you provide — no conversation history. Use `task_preset: "retrieval"` when the worker should search external knowledge tools (such as QMD via MCP) and return synthesized evidence with provenance instead of a raw tool dump.{opencode_note}

If OpenCode is enabled and the task is coding-heavy (multi-file edits, debugging, refactors), set `worker_type` to `"opencode"` and include a `directory`.
